Turks Smoke Less after Smoking Ban Applied, Hurriyet Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-15T06:07:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/turks-smoke-less-after-smoking-ban-applied-hurriyet-reports.html
Turkish cigarette consumption fell
last year as a nationwide ban on smoking in public places took
force, Hurriyet newspaper reported.  The number of cigarettes sold fell to 93.4 billion in 2010
from 107.6 billion in 2009, the Istanbul-based newspaper
reported, citing figures from the tobacco and alcohol regulator.  Turks spend an average of 18 billion liras ($11.4 billion)
a year on cigarettes, it said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
